<HEADLINE>
<P>
KOOP TO RETIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Many thanks to the retiring U.S. surgeon general, Dr. C. Everett Koop. How 
refreshing to have had a leader who respected us, who told us the truth! His 
insistence on "our right to know" was proof of that respect. 
</P>
<P>
His anti-smoking message, his enlightened, humane concern for AIDS victims and 
his campaign for sex education show what a difference one person can make. 
</P>
<P>
He has been a vitally important voice. That voice will be missed. 
</P>
<P>
R. KAHN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
