<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: L.A. COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parsons Corp., a Pasadena-based international engineering and construction 
group, announced that Ray W. Judson has been appointed president. William E. 
Leonhard, chairman and chief executive, also announced the following changes: 
</P>
<P>
Chief Financial Officer Thomas L. Langford was elected to the board and 
promoted to executive vice president. Leonard J. Pieroni was promoted to 
executive vice president-director of business development. Robert B. Sheh 
replaced Judson as president of the Ralph M. Parsons Co. subsidiary, and 
William E. Hall was named senior vice president of RMP. 
</P>
<P>
The RMP unit also announced the promotions of Dennis E. Pisula to vice 
president-petroleum and chemical division, and Sanford Holst to vice president 
and manager, management systems department. 
</P>
