<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: LEGAL FILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Claudia Puig, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Atlanta resident has accused actor Rob Lowe in a civil lawsuit of making 
sexual videotapes with a minor female. The lawsuit was filed against the Brat 
Pack star on Friday in Fulton County State Court. The lawsuit alleges that Lowe 
seduced a minor into appearing in the tapes with him and another person while 
he was in Atlanta for last summer's Democratic National Convention. The lawsuit 
contends the 25-year-old actor "used his celebrity status as an inducement to 
females to engage in sexual intercourse, sodomy and multiple party sexual 
activity for his immediate sexual gratification and for the purpose of making 
pornographic films of these activities." The lawsuit, obtained by an Atlanta 
television station, was sealed within an hour of its filing. Fulton County 
Dist. Atty. Lewis Slaton said he has a copy of the tape and is reviewing it to 
determine whether criminal charges would be filed. Criminal charges would 
include allegations that Lowe violated Georgia statutes involving the making of 
pornographic movies with minors, Slaton said. The penalty upon a conviction is 
1 to 20 years in prison. Lowe was out of the country an unavailable for 
comment. Claudia Puig 
</P>
</TEXT>
