<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DRIVER SOUGHT IN DEATH OF MAN HIT BY PICKUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A25-year-old Sun Valley man was killed in a hit-and-run accident at a North 
Hollywood intersection, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Ricardo Estrada was taken to St. Joseph Medical Center in Burbank immediately 
after the accident about 8 p.m. Saturday at Tujunga Avenue and Hartland Street, 
said Officer Mel Scholl of the Los Angeles Police Department. Estrada died a 
short time later, Scholl said. 
</P>
<P>
A witness told police that Estrada was walking east across Tujunga Avenue when 
he was struck by a red Toyota pickup truck heading north. The driver of the 
truck failed to stop and was last seen heading west on Vanowen Street, Scholl 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
