<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAPANESE PAIR WINS 300-KILOMETER RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SENDAI, Japan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Japanese team of Kazuyoshi Hoshino and Moto Kitano drove their Nissan 
Skyline to victory Sunday in the Highland 300-kilometer championship race. 
</P>
<P>
Hoshino and Kitano sped 80 laps over the 2.33-mile Highland Circuit in northern 
Japan in 2 hours 30 minutes 26.825 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Also driving a Nissan Skyline, Masahiro Hasumi of Japan and Anders Olofsson of 
Sweden came in second in 2:30:42.278, followed by Kenichi Tsuchiya and 
Britain's Kris Hodgetts, in a Ford Sierra, in 2:31:50.909. 
</P>
<P>
A total of 32 cars started and 27 completed the race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
