<P>
SHOT FROM CAR WOUNDS MAN AT CENTENNIAL PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A shot from a passing car wounded a 21-year-old man as he walked through 
Centennial Regional Park in Santa Ana on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Officers said Manuel Santos of Paramount was treated at UCI Medical Center for 
a groin wound and was released. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana police said they did not believe the shooting was related to gangs. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting occurred shortly before 2 p.m. 
</P>
