<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: LAGUNA HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
POST OFFICE ON WHEELS OPENS IN LEISURE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A "post office on wheels" opened for business last week in Leisure World. 
</P>
<P>
The new postal service consists of three 2 1/2-ton postal vans to be parked 
from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. at Clubhouse 3 on Mondays and at Clubhouse 5 on Fridays. 
Nearly all services available at post office retail lobbies will be available 
in the mobile vans, including first-class mail; express mail; priority mail; 
parcel post; certified, registered and insured mail; stamps; money orders, and 
international services. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana field division Postmaster Hector G. Godinez said the aim was to make 
postal business more convenient for residents of Leisure World. 
</P>
</TEXT>
