<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE SOFTBALL; 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON LOSES TITLE GAME, 2-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AL PRESTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cami Allen pitched a four-hitter and Palomar College took advantage of a key 
Fullerton error in the sixth to score both its runs en route to winning the 
state community college softball championship, 2-0, Sunday at Golden West 
College. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier Sunday, Fullerton's Kristin Jacobs pitched a four-hitter to hand 
Palomar its first defeat of the double-elimination tournament, 2-0, and force 
the second game. 
</P>
<P>
Palomar (39-6) opened the bottom of the sixth of the second game with singles 
by Christie Westerlund and Kenda Leffler. Palomar got a big break one out later 
when left fielder Dena Oburn dropped a soft line drive by Allen to load the 
bases. 
</P>
<P>
Westerlund, who went to third on Oburn's error, scored on Jodi Williams' 
infield out. Leffler scored on Jessica Camacho's single. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton (39-12) threatened against Allen (28-5) in the seventh when, with one 
out, Pita Licon walked and Christy Richmond and Debbie Wagner singled to load 
the bases. But Kelly Hilliard hit into a double play. 
</P>
<P>
"I felt we could hit against them, but we made too many mistakes," said 
Fullerton Coach Margo Davis, who is retiring after 31 years at the school. "You 
can't let a good team off the hook the way we did today." 
</P>
<P>
Jacobs (35-9), who had 19 consecutive scoreless innings before Palomar scored, 
scattered six hits in the loss. 
</P>
<P>
In the first game, Jacobs gave Fullerton a 1-0 lead with an RBI single in the 
fourth inning. Debbie Wagner, who doubled and moved to third on Hilliard's 
sacrifice to start the fifth, scored Fullerton's second run on a bunt by Kelli 
Johnson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
