<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Orange County residents placed among the winners of the 9th annual Music 
City Song Festival, a national competition for profesional and amateur singers 
and songwriters. William G. Hinkle of Laguna Niguel won a $500 first prize in 
the Middle-of-the-Road/Adult Contemporary vocal category for his song, "I'm All 
Brand New." Ronald Valdez of Fountain Valley came in second in the Amateur 
Pop/Top 40 songwriting category for "Distant Heart," co-written with Susan 
Stevens of North Hollywood. Doreen Campbell of Cypress placed third in the 
Pop/Top 40 song lyrics competition for her lyrics to "How Did I Fall for You?" 
</P>
<P>
The Nashville-based competition is judged by panels of music-industry 
professionals who review taped entries or lyric sheets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
